   "id": "intro-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# üëÅÔ∏è CUBO Multimodal & OCR Guide\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how CUBO handles scanned documents, images, and complex layouts using OCR and Vision models.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Processing Capabilities\n",
    "| Format | Logic | Method |\n",
    "| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
    "| **Digital PDF** | Native Extraction | `pdfplumber` |\n",
    "| **Scanned PDF** | OCR Fallback | `Tesseract` |\n",
    "| **Images** | Direct OCR | `pytesseract` |\n",
    "| **Complex Docs** | Visual Reasoning | `Vision VL` |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "setup-code",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add CUBO to path\n",
    "cubo_root = Path(\".\").resolve().parent\n",
    "if str(cubo_root) not in sys.path:\n",
    "    sys.path.insert(0, str(cubo_root))\n",
    "\n",
    "from cubo.config import config\n",
    "print(f\"CUBO root: {cubo_root}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ocr-check-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1Ô∏è‚É£ OCR Environment Check\n",
    "\n",
    "CUBO uses Tesseract for local, private OCR. Let's verify it is installed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "tesseract-check-code",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import subprocess\n",
    "\n",
    "def check_tesseract():\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        result = subprocess.run(['tesseract', '--version'], capture_output=True, text=True)\n",
    "        return True, result.stdout.split('\\n')[0]\n",
    "    except FileNotFoundError:\n",
    "        return False, None\n",
    "\n",
    "available, version = check_tesseract()\n",
    "print(f\"Tesseract OCR: {\'‚úÖ \' + version if available else \'‚ùå Not installed\'}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "processor-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Using the Modern OCR Processor\n",
    "\n",
    "CUBO's `OCRProcessor` is automatically used by the `DeepIngestor` when a PDF has no selectable text."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "processor-init-code",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from cubo.ingestion.ocr_processor import OCRProcessor\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize processor using global config\n",
    "processor = OCRProcessor(config)\n",
    "print(f\"‚úÖ OCR Processor Initialized (Enabled: {processor.enabled})\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "deep-ingest-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3Ô∏è‚É£ Deep Ingestion with Automated OCR\n",
    "\n",
    "The `DeepIngestor` is the recommended way to process batches of documents. It handles OCR fallbacks and table extraction transparently."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "deep-ingest-demo-code",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from cubo.ingestion.deep_ingestor import DeepIngestor\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a small sample folder\n",
    "os.makedirs(\"ocr_sample\", exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1. Setup ingestor\n",
    "ingestor = DeepIngestor(input_folder=\"ocr_sample\", output_dir=\"./data/deep\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"üöÄ Starting deep ingestion...\")\n",
    "print(\"   (This will automatically detect if OCR is needed per file)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Check path\n",
    "print(f\"‚úÖ DeepIngestor ready. Target: {ingestor.input_folder.absolute()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "Vision-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4Ô∏è‚É£ Vision Integration\n",
    "\n",
    "For complex documents, CUBO can use the Vision-language model to understand layouts:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "Vision-init-code",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "try:\n",
    "    from cubo.models.vision_processor import VisionProcessor\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Note: This model is heavy (~400MB)\n",
    "    vision = VisionProcessor()\n",
    "    print(f\"Vision: ‚úÖ Ready (Device: {Vision.device})\")\n",
    "except ImportError:\n",
    "    print(\"‚ÑπÔ∏è Vision processor not available\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "tips-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## üéØ Best Practices\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Resolution**: 300 DPI is the sweet spot for Tesseract.\n",
    "2. **Multilingual**: Ensure you have Tesseract language packs (`tessdata`) for non-English docs.\n",
    "3. **Memory**: Use the `DeepIngestor` for large PDF sets to avoid RAM spikes."
   ]
  }
